Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pop the @butternut squash{300%g}(diced) onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{20-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Once cooked, remove from the oven and set aside.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(diced) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Boil your #kettle{}, then pour the @water{450%ml} for the risotto into a #measuring jug{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat (if you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal #saucepan{} and transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} later).

Once the pan is hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and onion. Stir-fry until golden and softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add half the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @risotto rice{175%g}, then stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the boiled water from your measuring jug and @vegetable stock paste{20%g} to the rice and stir well to combine.

Bring back up to the boil, then pop a lid on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Squeeze some lemon juice into a #medium bowl{} and mix in the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season, then set your dressing aside.

When the risotto has about 10 mins of cooking time remaining, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @monkfish medallions{200%g} and cook for ~{3-4%minutes} each side, adjusting the heat as necessary.

Add half the @unsalted butter{20%g} and the remaining garlic to the pan, then cook for ~{1%minute} more, spooning the butter all over the fish. Remove from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. The monkfish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in roasted butternut squash, lemon zest, @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) and remaining butter. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Add the @wild rocket{20%g} to dressing and toss to coat, then share the risotto between your #bowls{} and top with the monkfish on one side and the rocket salad on the other.

Sprinkle over the @red chilli flakes{1%tsp} to finish (use less if you don't like heat). Enjoy!